<HEADLINE>
FT  10 AUG 94 / Shiver me timbers
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Mary Rose, the warship raised from the seabed in 1982, has now been
reassembled in the condition in which it was found with the replacement of a
final timber - a bracket supporting screens to protect archers. The ship, on
display in Portsmouth, was built between 1509 and 1511 on the orders of
Henry VIII and sank in 1545.
</TEXT>
