   LONDON
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
US Secretary of State Warren Christopher yesterday endorsed easing sanctions
against Serbia if Belgrade keeps its promise to stop aiding the Bosnian
Serbs. 'If there is a substantial period of enforcement, if the border was
effectively closed and if the Bosnian Serbs seem to be deprived of important
aid and war-making material, clearly there then would be a case for easing
