move would endanger allied peacekeeping efforts. Bosnian government troops,
meanwhile, are overrunning Moslem separatist positions in the Bihac region,
sending thousands of civilians and rebel soldiers fleeing across the border
into neighbouring Croatia, according to United Nations officials. Government
forces have made big advances against rebels who backed local business
tycoon Mr Fikret Abdic, a former member of the Bosnian leadership, who split
with Sarajevo almost a year ago over whether to accept an international
peace plan for Bosnia.
