<HEADLINE>
FT  10 AUG 94 / World News in Brief: Three months' grace for Pounds 7.6m
statue
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Campaigners hoping to keep Canova's The Three Graces in Britain were given
an extra three months to raise the money needed to stop the statue going to
the Getty Museum in California which has bought it for Pounds 7.6m. The
decision by national heritage secretary Stephen Dorrell follows the
announcement of a joint rescue package by the London-based Victoria and
Albert museum and the National Gallery of Scotland in Edinburgh. They have
committed Pounds 1m to the fund set up to buy the work, which has reached
Pounds 5.8m.
</TEXT>
