<HEADLINE>
FT  09 AUG 94 / International Company News: SNC-Lavalin posts sharp
increases
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ROBERT GIBBENS
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   MONTREAL
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
SNC-Lavalin, a Canadian-based international engineering and construction
group, posted sharp increases in second-quarter and half-year earnings
thanks to improving margins and lower interest costs.
First-half profit was CDollars 14.7m, or 94 cents a share, up from Dollars
8.8m, or 60 cents, a year earlier, on revenues of Dollars 397m, a rise of 11
per cent.
Second-quarter profit equalled 57 cents, against 43 cents on revenues of
Dollars 217m, up from Dollars 184m.
