<HEADLINE>
FT  09 AUG 94 / World Commodities Prices: Tea
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
There was an improved and more general demand, reports the Tea Brokers'
Association. Brightest east African teas were fully firm and medium
descriptions sold readily at firm to dearer rates. Plainer sorts remained
about steady. Ceylons were well supported with brighter teas often gaining
several pence. The small selection on offer met good demand at firm rates.
Quotations: best available 174p/kg, good 158p/kg, good medium 140p/kg,
medium 122p/kg, low medium 84p/kg. The highest price realised this week was
186p/kg for a Kenya pf. 1.
</TEXT>
