FT  09 AUG 94 / Commodities and Agriculture: PNG gold mine back in operation
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By NIKKI TAIT
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   SYDNEY
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
The large Porgera gold mine in the Enga province of Papua New Guinea, began
operating again at the weekend after an explosion last week which left 11
people missing, presumed dead. The blast occurred at the explosives
facility, a short distance from the mine.
The project is one of the largest gold mines outside South Africa and an
important revenue source for the PNG government which has a 25 per cent
interest in it. Similar stakes are held by Placer Pacific, Renison
Goldfields and Highlands Gold.
BHP Coal Australia yesterday shut down coalmining operations at Moura in
Queensland, as rescue teams tried to reach 11 people trapped underground in
an accident on Sunday night. The mine has taken a heavy toll in the past: 12
people were killed there in 1986 and 13 in 1975.
