<HEADLINE>
FT  09 AUG 94 / The Lex Column: British Airways
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The 3 per cent fall in British Airways' share price yesterday suggests the
market had exaggerated expectations about the effect of economic recovery on
its operations. Still, the actual outturn is not bad. BA has managed
impressive growth in lucrative premium traffic business. Its more efficient
use of aircraft promises enhanced gains as the recovery proceeds.
There are more grounds for worry on strategic alliances. Yesterday's figures
suggest disappointing progress in reducing losses at European associates. BA
calculates USAir will contribute around Pounds 70m to profits this year
whatever happens to its investment in balance sheet terms. The airline could
easily afford to write down its stake. Whether it could afford the resulting
loss of strategic direction is another matter.
</TEXT>
