<HEADLINE>
FT  09 AUG 94 / World Trade News: Alcatel
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By JOHN RIDDING
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   PARIS
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
ALCATEL, the French telecommunications group, yesterday announced an
expansion of its presence in the South African market with the conclusion of
a FFr210m (Dollars 39m) contract to supply a telephone transmission network
to Eksom, the South African electricity board, writes John Ridding in Paris.
The five-year contract, which was won by Alcatel Italia, the company's
Italian subsidiary, includes the supply of medium and high capacity digital
radio links and a network management centre.
</TEXT>
