FT  09 AUG 94 / Kuchma issues two decrees
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   KIEV
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
President Leonid Kuchma issued two decrees yesterday putting himself
directly in charge of government and subordinating all local councils to the
presidency, state television said, Reuter reports from Kiev. Under the first
decree the president will define the government's basic direction and
priorities and appoint and sack the heads of powerful state committees. Mr
Vitaly Mosol will remain as prime minister. The move was explained in the
decree as necessary to 'put into effect economic reforms and develop market
relations'. The second decree subordinates the heads of Ukraine's 27
regional councils directly to the president. Lesser councils must then
report to the regional councils.
Earlier, Mr Kuchma issued the first of a planned series of decrees aimed at
reforming the economy. Under it financial assistance to state enterprises,
mostly in the form of loans, will be given only after they provide a
business plan or restructuring programme.
