<HEADLINE>
FT  09 AUG 94 / Czech capital inflows rise
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By VINCENT BOLAND
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   PRAGUE
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
The Czech National Bank has revised sharply upwards its estimate of foreign
capital inflows for 1994 from Kcs60bn (Pounds 1.38bn) to Kcs100bn, but
stressed that the inflationary effect would be broadly neutral. The pace of
foreign capital inflows has pushed up M2 money supply to a preliminary 7.4
per cent in June from 3.7 per cent in April, and an average 1.3 per cent in
the first quarter of 1994. Year-on-year inflation in June was 9.7 per cent,
up from 9.3 per cent in May and 9.2 per cent in April, and close to the
target of 10 per cent set by the CNB at the beginning of the year.
