<DATELINE>
   SARAJEVO
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
The commander of UN troops in Bosnia called yesterday for a demilitarised
zone around Sarajevo after Nato aircraft struck at defiant Serbs last
Friday. Lt-Gen Sir Michael Rose was trying to set up a meeting with the
commander of the Bosnian Serb forces, Gen Ratko Mladic, to discuss the
issue, a UN official said. The plan calls for a withdrawal of all armed and
uniformed soldiers and would allow both Serb and Moslem forces to take their
weapons out of the zone for use elsewhere. However, there has been no
response from Gen Mladic, whose forces in Sarajevo have been blamed for an
increasing number of sniping incidents. UN sharpshooters are reported to
havekilled one or two Serb snipers in the past two days.
