<HEADLINE>
FT  08 AUG 94 / Observer: Hyper-market
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Whatever do the initials 'CHyp' after a person's name denote? If that person
is Tom Leigh, director of 3T Publications, one of the companies now in
provisional liquidation thanks to the UK government's clamp-down on
'pyramid' schemes, the logical conclusion might be 'Certificate in Hype'. It
transpires instead, in a letter circulated by 3T, that Leigh is trained as a
hypnotherapist at the 'well-known and highly-respected Proudfoot School of
Hypnosis and Psychotherapy at Scarborough'. Here at last an explanation as
to why all those 'investors' opened their wallets with such alacrity to a
notion so fundamentally flawed?
</TEXT>
